Your plan must be executor-ready for unattended development. The submitted artifact must:
- Capture the problem context and the concrete user-facing outcome
- Break the work into ordered implementation steps with enough detail to execute without re-planning
- Identify the critical files or subsystems to inspect or modify and why they matter
- Call out major risks, edge cases, and the mitigation for each
- Define verification that the development agent can run to prove completion
- Include work_units when the work can be parallelized safely
- Make the planning-to-development handoff explicit so the development agent can start immediately

Prefer concrete actions and acceptance criteria over vague advice. This is an unattended pipeline: do not ask for clarification, do not defer decisions, and do not leave the executor to infer missing structure.

Call `{{SUBMIT_ARTIFACT_TOOL_NAME}}` with artifact_type="plan" and content as a JSON string conforming to the plan schema.

The `content` argument must be a JSON string whose decoded object is the RAW plan payload.
Do NOT wrap the payload in outer `type` or `content` fields. Ralph adds artifact metadata itself.

Your payload must decode to an object shaped like this:

```json
{
  "summary": {
    "context": "What is being changed, why it matters, and what the executor should accomplish.",
    "scope_items": [
      {"text": "Concrete outcome 1", "count": "optional quantity", "category": "optional category"},
      {"text": "Concrete outcome 2", "count": "optional quantity", "category": "optional category"},
      {"text": "Concrete outcome 3", "count": "optional quantity", "category": "optional category"}
    ]
  },
  "skills_mcp": {
    "skills": ["optional skill names"],
    "mcps": ["optional MCP server names"]
  },
  "steps": [
    {
      "number": 1,
      "title": "Imperative step title",
      "content": "Detailed executor-ready instructions. Assume a weaker model will follow this literally.",
      "step_type": "file_change",
      "priority": "high",
      "targets": [
        {"path": "path/to/file.py", "action": "modify"}
      ],
      "location": "optional module or function",
      "rationale": "optional reason this step exists",
      "depends_on": []
    }
  ],
  "critical_files": {
    "primary_files": [
      {"path": "path/to/file.py", "action": "modify", "estimated_changes": "optional scope estimate"}
    ],
    "reference_files": [
      {"path": "path/to/example.py", "purpose": "optional reference or pattern to follow"}
    ]
  },
  "risks_mitigations": [
    {"risk": "Specific failure mode", "mitigation": "How to avoid or detect it", "severity": "medium"}
  ],
  "verification_strategy": [
    {"method": "Exact command or check", "expected_outcome": "What success looks like"}
  ],
  "parallel_plan": [
    {
      "id": "optional-parallel-unit",
      "description": "Optional safe-to-parallelize work chunk",
      "edit_area": {"paths": ["path/to/file.py"], "directories": ["optional/dir"]},
      "depends_on": []
    }
  ],
  "work_units": []
}
```

Hard requirements for the payload:
- `summary.scope_items` must contain at least 3 concrete items.
- `steps` must contain at least 1 step, and every step must be explicit enough for a weaker agent to execute without re-planning.
- `critical_files.primary_files` must contain at least 1 file.
- `targets[*].action` and `critical_files.primary_files[*].action` must be one of `create`, `modify`, or `delete`.
- `risks_mitigations` must contain at least 1 real risk with a mitigation.
- `verification_strategy` must contain exact commands/checks, not vague statements.
- Include `work_units` only when parallel work is genuinely safe; otherwise omit it or use an empty array.
